Hey all,

Quick status update — the changes we're working through require broad testing, so we want as much time as possible to work through all scenarios while still releasing in time for you to cut off NAV Load Lists on March 2nd.

Plan: Release Thursday night. You'll have Friday to review everything before the cutoff. We'll walk through it all on Wednesday, but as tasks are ready to test in Red, we'll let you know so you can jump in early. Release notes coming soon.

 

DBR Updates

  • Qty Overrides / Undo Overrides — Ready to review in Red
  • Create Sessions / Historical Sales / Shipdate — Ready to review in Red
  • Demand Calc Algorithm — In Progress
  • Order Submit Workflow — Awaiting Testing (confirming BPTest hookup)
  • Reserve/Allocate % — In Progress, close to done
  • Missing Item & Location Fields — Checking with dev for update

 

Load List Fixes

  • Completed: Must-Go availability, in-transit sync (30min→1min), order qty deleting on refresh, container codes auto-fill, inventory mismatch/duplicates — all resolved
  • Next Release: Station dropdown limit, pinned totals recalc on filter
  • Needs Testing: Full customer/item sync (covers missing routes, Station 234, missing locations)
  • In Progress: In-session refresh (may not make Thursday)

 

Inventory / Mobile Apps

  • 4 items in testing, ready for Red review soon (0-qty assignment bug, Organic receiving bug, Variant Support, Organic Lot numbers)
  • Resolved: Posting Date issue (bad Nav location disabled)
  • Retail Scans for new WM Stores — No scan data found
  • In Progress: Finish Inv not matching Nav (team working on fix)

 

Let me know if you have any questions!
